# Operational Analytics Tools

## Overview

Operational analytics tools allow wholesale organizations to monitor performance, analyze operational trends, and support decision making through data visualization and reporting.

These tools combine data from ERP systems, warehouse management platforms, and financial systems to provide operational visibility.

---

## Common Analytics Tools

Wholesale operations teams commonly use tools such as:

• Microsoft Excel  
• Google Sheets  
• Tableau  
• Power BI  
• ERP reporting dashboards  

These tools allow teams to track key operational metrics.

---

## Use Cases

Analytics tools are typically used to monitor:

• order processing performance  
• inventory availability  
• shipment execution  
• chargeback trends  
• invoice accuracy  

Visual dashboards help teams identify issues quickly.

---

## Data Sources

Analytics tools often pull data from:

• ERP systems  
• warehouse management systems (WMS)  
• EDI platforms  
• financial systems  
• inventory management systems  

Combining these sources provides a comprehensive view of operations.

---

## Operational Benefits

Analytics tools help organizations:

• detect operational issues early  
• monitor performance trends  
• support operational decision making  
• improve reporting transparency  

These insights strengthen operational efficiency.

---

## Final Note

Analytics tools transform operational data into meaningful insights. When organizations use data effectively, they can improve performance and maintain greater control over wholesale operations.
